alert.note: Alert for Eastern Aleutians (Alaska) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 19 at 4:12PM AKST until February 20 at 5:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM TO 5 PM AKST SUNDAY... * WHAT...Southeast winds 50 to 65 mph with gusts up to 80 mph possible. * WHERE...Eastern Aleutians. * WHEN...From 7 AM to 5 PM AKST Sunday. * IMPACTS...High winds could move loose debris, damage property, and cause power outages. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong southeast winds associated with a strengthening low pressure system in the North Pacific will gradually turn south to southwest Sunday morning. Winds are expected to peak Sunday morning and remain elevated through Sunday early afternoon before slowly diminishing Sunday evening.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind. Prepare for the possibility of widespread power outages. Use caution if you must drive.
